files.patch:
@@ -243,1 +243,2 @@
-  # leading spaces.
+  # leading spaces. There may also be multiple entries on the same line, so start
+  # with splitting such lines.
@@ -246,3 +247,6 @@
-	    -e 's|^\([ ]*\)\./|\1|' \
-	    -e '/^[ ]*[^/ ]/s|^\([ ]*\)|\1$(WORKSPACE_ROOT)/|' \
-	    $1.tmp > $1
+	    -e 's|\([^ ]\) \{1,\}\([^\\:]\)|\1 \\\n \2|g' \
+	    $1.tmp \
+	    | $(SED) \
+	        -e 's|^\([ ]*\)\./|\1|' \
+	        -e '/^[ ]*[^/ ]/s|^\([ ]*\)|\1$(WORKSPACE_ROOT)/|' \
+	        > $1
